  "title": "Assistant Project Manager/ Project Manager (Construction)",
  "description": "<p>Our esteemed client in the <strong>Construction industry</strong> is seeking an <strong>Assistant Project Manager/ Project Manager </strong>to join their dynamic team:</p><ul><li><strong>Employment Type: </strong>Permanent</li><li><strong>Position:</strong> Assistant Project Manager/ Project Manager</li><li><strong>Location:</strong> Islandwide</li><li><strong>Working Hours:</strong> 5.5 days, Office Hours</li><li><strong>Salary Package:</strong> Up to $11,000 + Bonus</li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>To support the planning, scheduling, and coordinating project activities to meet timeline, cost, and quality objectives</li><li>Monitor project progress, identify risks or issues, and implement corrective actions as needed</li><li>Verify construction plans, drawings, and specifications to ensure accuracy and identify any potential errors, defects, or variations</li><li>Liaise with subcontractors, consultants, architects, and relevant authorities, providing guidance and technical support to the project team</li><li>Support personnel management, including coaching and monitoring team productivity</li><li>Drive continuous improvement initiatives to enhance project efficiency and performance</li><li>Organize and lead regular coordination meetings, track deliverables, and maintain project documentation</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least Degree in Civil Engineering or related discipline.</li><li>Minimum 7 years of construction experience, ideally with a main contractor</li><li>Strong project management skills, including planning, scheduling, and milestone tracking</li><li>Familiarity with construction quality, cost, and safety standards</li><li>Comfortable working across multiple sites if required.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office & Project Management software.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Ready to apply? Here’s how:</strong></p><ul><li>Click the APPLY button, or</li><li>Email your resume (in MS Word or PDF format) to<strong> </strong><a href=\"mailto:adelin@intuitrecruitment.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>adelin@intuitrecruitment.com</strong>.</a> Include the job title in your email subject line for prompt processing.</li></ul><p><em><strong>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></em><br /></p><p>By submitting your application, you consent to the collection and use of your personal data under Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA).<br /></p><p>Adelin Chong | EA Personnel Reg No.: R1875641</p><p>Intuit Recruitment Pte Ltd | EA License No.: 25C2793</p>",
